<h2>Clear Glass Walls</h2>
Our clear glass walls create a seamless wall with uninhibited views. The unitâ€™s non-thermal design makes it a great choice for interior room dividers, but Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup> can engineer the clear glass wall for exterior use as well, making it an ideal product selection for stadium suites. Panels are typically top hung, however, bottom load sliding options are also available. Â Solarâ€™s clear glass walls can be designed to operate with multiple configurations. The non-thermal clear glass walls are typically used for interior and light exterior applications. No vertical frame is required; however, Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup> offers mono seal and dual-seal insulating frames that are recommended when the clear glass wall system will be utilized for outdoor applications.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-36869" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/commerical-clear-glass-walls.png" alt="" width="680" height="380" /></h2>
<h2>Glass with Narrow Profile Frame</h2>
A glass with narrow profile aluminum frame style has a narrow metal frame on the verticals as well as the top and bottom of each glass panel. Â This design is highly recommended for outdoor applications, as it is the best option for preventing sound, air, and water transmittance.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36867 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/cgw-kent-state-glass-to-glass.png" alt="Kent State University Clear Glass Walls" width="680" height="380" /></h2>
<h2>Glass to Glass</h2>
In a glass to glass style, the glass edges are completely exposed and there is no vertical framing. This is only recommended for interior use because sound, air, and water can easily pass through the small gaps between the panels.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-36868" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/clear-glass-walls-cincinnati-reds-suite.png" alt="Commercial Clear Glass Walls for Stadium" width="680" height="380" /></h2>
<h2>Glass with Gasket</h2>
In a glass with gasket style, the framing has gaskets attached to the vertical sides of each glass panel that touch when the wall is closed and help reduce sound, air, and water transmittance.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="36871" img_size="full"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2>Non-thermal Aluminum</h2>
Non-thermal aluminum framework is used on all three styles. The aluminum will not rust, rot or require constant finish maintenance. The non-thermal frame is suitable for interior applications because there is no need for insulation because the doors are used on the interior of a space. If your job requires a thermally isolated clear wall please contact your Solar Innovations, Inc. representative to discuss options.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36899 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/engineering-icon.png" alt="Custom Engineering for Custom Glazed Windows and Doors" width="120" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Custom Engineered</h2>
Each Solar Innovations systemÂ is custom made to order based on your project needs and preferences. Our team of engineering experts has you covered.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36897 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/made-in-usa-icon.png" alt="Made in the USA" width="159" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Made in America</h2>
All our products are designed and manufactured in the United States at our state-of-the-art facility in Pine Grove, PA.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36822 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Ease-of-Operation-icon-small-1.png" alt="" width="69" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Ease of Operation</h2>
Solar Innovations' systems offer single-handed operation and move smoothly with little effort. Much of our hardware is manufactured in house which allows us to control lead times.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36827 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/monster-sizes-icon-small.png" alt="" width="62" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Monsterous Sizes</h2>
Solar Innovations has the ability to manufacture even larger panels that operate with greater ease for several functions: folding, sliding, swinging, and stacking.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]<code>[video_lightbox_youtube video_id="Pc6FS4ayAn8" width="679" height="403" anchor="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/CGW-video.png"  alt="clear glass walls"]</code>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]<img class="alignright wp-image-36916 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/clear_glass_wall_iso-2.gif" alt="" width="300" height="265" />
<h2>Hardware</h2>
Security is always a concern with doors. Traditional hardware cannot be utilized on the doors. Instead of locking by way of the lever, these doors lock with a floor lock. Depending on configuration, operable panels can be utilized within the unit and this door can be locked in place. The hardware used for Solar InnovationsÂ® clear wall units is all of the highest quality. All helical bearings, in the head, are constructed out of stainless steel, which is corrosion resistant. The gaskets used on two of the models are available in both black and clear, which allows for more design options and visual cohesiveness.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_tabs style="flat" shape="square" active_section="1"][vc_tta_section i_icon_fontawesome="fa fa-info-circle" add_icon="true" title="Product Overview" tab_id="1469029847942-5f146428-b4cc"][vc_column_text]<a href="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/SI3000C-Clear-Glass-Walls-Stacking-Folding-Sliding.pdf"><img class="alignright wp-image-25556 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/coverpage1.png" alt="" width="400" height="248" /></a>

Solar Innovations SI3000C Clear Glass Walls maximize transparency for stadium suites, balcony enclosures, interior operable partitions, etc. Individual top load bearing clearÂ glass panels are made to a maximum panel size of 3' x 10', or possibly larger while offering some protection from wind. Aluminum profiles capture the head and sill, while the vertical edges of the glass remain free. When the doors are open, they can be neatly stacked or pocketed away in a remote location. Special gaskets can be used to provide a minimal level of air and water performance upon request.

